Debian installation
===================

Base system
sudo apt-get install python-wxgtk2.6 python-numpy python-tables python-scipy python-matplotlib python-networkx

Plugins

Graphics/ThreeDFrame
sudo apt-get install python-vtk

Statistics/kmeans
sudo apt-get install python-biopython

Statistics/Kde and Statistics/bayes
sudo apt-get install scons libboost-dev r-mathlib blitz++ lapack3-dev

# install the ANN library (for kde)
cd /tmp
wget http://www.cs.umd.edu/~mount/ANN/Files/1.1.1/ann_1.1.1.tar.gz
tar -xzf ann_1.1.1.tar.gz
cd ann_1.1.1/
make linux-g++
sudo mv ann_1.1.1 /usr/local/src

# install the boost numeric binding headers (for bayes)
cd /tmp
wget http://news.tiker.net/news.tiker.net/download/software/boost-bindings/boost-bindings-20070826.tar.gz
tar -xzf boost-bindings-20070826.tar.gz
sudo cp -R boost-bindings/boost/numeric/bindings/ /usr/include/boost/numeric/

# build the python shared librarie
cd $FLOW/src
scons install

Projections/ica
sudo apt-get install python-rpy r-base
sudo R
> install.packages("fastICA")

Mac OS X installation
=====================

Download and install setuptools from http://pypi.python.org/pypi/setuptools
tar -xzf setuptools-0.6c8.tar.gz 
cd setuptools-0.6c8
sudo python setup.py install

Download and install wxPython from http://www.wxpython.org/
Here's a slightly nutty way to do it all from the command line
cd /tmp
wget http://superb-east.dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/wxpython/wxPython2.8-osx-unicode-2.8.7.1-universal-py2.5.dmg
hdid wxPython2.8-osx-unicode-2.8.7.1-universal-py2.5.dmg 
cd /Volumes/wxPython2.8-osx-unicode-2.8.7.1-universal-py2.5/
sudo installer -package wxPython2.8-osx-unicode-universal-py2.5.pkg -target /Volumes/Macintosh\ HD

wget http://pypi.python.org/packages/source/n/networkx/networkx-0.36.tar.gz
tar -xzf networkx-0.36.tar.gz 
cd networkx-0.36
python setup.py build
sudo python setup.py install

wget http://www.pytables.org/download/stable/pytables-2.0.3.tar.gz
tar -xzf pytables-2.0.3.tar.gz 
cd pytables-2.0.3
python setup.py build
sudo python setup.py install

Install the Scipy superpack from 
http://idisk.mac.com/fonnesbeck-Public/ScipySuperpackInstaller.zip

Alternatively, individual packages can be downloaded and installed from
http://pythonmac.org/packages/py25-fat/index.html

Install R from source
wget http://cran.r-project.org/src/base/R-2/R-2.6.2.tar.gz
tar -xzf R-2.6.2.tar.gz
cd R-2.6.2.tar.gz
./configure --enable-BLAS-shlib --with-blas='-framework vecLib'
make
sudo make install
cd src/nmath/standalone
make
sudo ln -s /Library/Frameworks/R.framework/Resources/R /usr/local/bin/R

Statistics/kmeans
wget http://downloads.sourceforge.net/numpy/Numeric-24.2.tar.gz

* Installing Qt
wget http://ftp.ntua.gr/pub/X11/Qt/qt/source/qt-mac-opensource-src-4.3.4.tar.gz
tar -xzf qt-mac-opensource-src-4.3.4.tar.gz
cd qt-mac-opensource-src-4.3.4
./configure
make
sudo make install

* Installing cmake
wget http://www.cmake.org/files/v2.4/cmake-2.4.8.tar.gz
tar -xzf cmake-2.4.8.tar.gz
cd cmake-2.4.8
./bootstrap
make
sudo make install

* Installing Paraview
export PATH=$PATH:/usr/local/Trolltech/Qt-4.3.4/
cvs -d :pserver:anoncvs@www.paraview.org:/cvsroot/ParaView3 login
cvs -d :pserver:anoncvs@www.paraview.org:/cvsroot/ParaView3 co ParaView3
mkdir ParaViewBuild
cd ParaViewBuild/
ccmake ../ParaView3
options (PARAVIEW_ENABLE_PYTHON ON)
Hit 'c' to configure and 'g' to generate Makefiles
make
sudo make install

* Installing VTK
cvs -d :pserver:anonymous@public.kitware.com:/cvsroot/VTK login
(respond with password vtk)
cvs -d :pserver:anonymous@public.kitware.com:/cvsroot/VTK checkout VTK
mkdir VTKBuild
cd VTKBuild
ccmake ../VTK
options (BUILD_SHARED_LIBS ON; VTK_WRAP_PYTHON ON)
Hit 'c' to configure and 'g' to generate Makefiles
make
sudo make install
cd Wrapping/Python
python setup.py build
sudo python setup.py install
export PYTHONPATH=/Library/Python/2.5/site-packages/VTK-5.1.0-py2.5.egg/vtk
